# Money Flow 2 — Agent Context Rules
# Read this before writing any code

## Project Overview
Personal finance app: expense tracking, cashback management, debt tracking.
Single user. Stack: Next.js 15 + Supabase (PostgreSQL) + Google Sheets sync.

## Database
- Source: `/supabase/migrations/*.sql` — this is the ONLY source of truth for schema
- Run `supabase db push` to apply migrations after changes
- NEVER hardcode balance or cashback calculations in application code — use DB triggers/views
- Balance is computed by trigger `txn_balance_sync` in migration 002
- Cashback is computed via view `v_cashback_cycle_summary` in migration 003
- Debt repaid_amount is synced by trigger `txn_debt_sync` in migration 004

## Transaction Rules
- `amount` is ALWAYS positive bigint in VND
- Direction determined by `type` field — never use negative numbers
- `status=void` = soft delete (never hard delete transactions)
- `persisted_cycle_tag` locks the cashback cycle (YYYY-MM format)
- Transfer = 2 rows: `transfer_out` + `transfer_in` (atomic)

## Parser API
- Raw text → JSON → `public.bulk_insert_parsed_txns(jsonb)` RPC
- LLM must output JSON matching schema in migration 007
- Two input formats are supported (see /docs/parser-formats.md)

## Sheets Sync
- Debt sheet sync is highest priority
- GAS script POSTs to `/api/sheets/sync` endpoint
- Endpoint reads from Supabase and returns formatted rows

## Code Style
- TypeScript strict mode
- Supabase client: `@supabase/supabase-js` v2
- API routes: Next.js App Router `/app/api/`
- No ORM — use Supabase client or raw SQL via RPC functions
- Avoid `any` types — generate types from `supabase gen types typescript`

## File Structure
```
/app/api/         - Next.js API routes
/supabase/        - migrations + config
/lib/supabase/    - client init + typed helpers
/docs/            - business logic docs
```
